properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 10 at 9:10PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation, Possibly Significant, Tonight
Through Saturday Night...

* WHAT...A mix of freezing rain and sleet this evening developing
from northwest to southeast will continue overnight and into
early Saturday morning. Total ice accumulations in excess of two
tenths of an inch are likely tonight into Saturday morning,
with some light sleet accumulation also possible. While
precipitation may lighten in intensity Saturday morning through
mid afternoon, a period of heavy snow is likely late Saturday
afternoon and evening. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches
are expected. Northeast winds will gust as high as 40 mph
overnight into Saturday and combined with ice and snow may cause
further impacts.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Illinois.

* WHEN...From 9 PM CST this evening to 3 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be significantly impacted at times,
especially overnight through early Saturday morning, and then
again later Saturday afternoon into Saturday night. Some power
outages and tree damage are possible due to the combination of
ice and wind. Patchy blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility later Saturday afternoon and night.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for Illinois can be obtained on the
internet at www.gettingaroundillinois.com.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST SUNDAY
